= Armistice signed in Matklingrad!

Officials from the Casoducrian Army and the Government have met with a delegation from Thoubia. For the Casoducrians, the leading delegates were Field Marshall Nicholas Kutyezov and the Prime Minister, Kalin Wilenski. For the Thoubians, their leading negotiators were Foreign Minister Rodzan von Aufenbeck and Ambassador to Casoducria, Johann Heidelmann.

After a preliminarcy cessation of hostilities were signed on June 4th, talks were held for several days to discuss the specifics of an armistice: The logistics of disasrming the threnches and several other specifics. In the end, the Armistice itself is not particularly harsh, altough the upcoming peace talks to be held in Spwe are guaranteed to be much harsher.

The news of an armistice are welcome in much of the war-weary populace of Casoducria and Orast in general, yet the Casoducrian Army and veterans are angered by the dishonest Thoubs for invading through neutral Kubloria. Still, the army will comply with the armistice. The Great War is over, after four brutal years, on June 15th, 1918.

